To run sdguikivy.py, kivy needs to be installed. Here follow the instructions to do so.
(internet is needed)

Installing kivy:
Windows: (https://kivy.org/docs/installation/installation-windows.html)
  Open the terminal and run one by one these lines:
    python -m pip install --upgrade pip wheel setuptools
    python -m pip install docutils pygments pypiwin32 kivy.deps.sdl2 kivy.deps.glew
    python -m pip install kivy.deps.gstreamer
    python -m pip install kivy
            
OS X: https://kivy.org/docs/installation/installation-osx.html
Linux: https://kivy.org/docs/installation/installation-linux.html

Installing matplotlib for kivy:    (https://kivy.org/docs/api-kivy.garden.html)
The garden module needs to be installed, though it might have already been installed when installing kivy.
Run these lines:
    pip install kivy-garden
    garden install matplotlib
